SIMPLE: slouch
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Slouch
<hw>Slouch</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. Icel.
<ets>sl<?/kr</ets>a slouching felloew, and E. <ets>slack</ets>,
<ets>slug</ets>, a lazy fellow.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A hanging down
of the head; a drooping attitude; a limp appearance; an ungainly,
clownish gait; a sidewise depression or hanging down, as of a hat
brim.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>An awkward, heavy, clownish fellow.</def>
<mark>[Colloq.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Slouth hat</b></col>, <cd>a soft, limp hat of unstiffened
cloth or felt.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Slouch</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Slouch
<hw>Slouch</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos>
<conjf>Slouched</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Slouching</conjf>.]</vmorph> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To droop, as the
head.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To walk in a clumsy, lazy manner.</def>
<mark>[Colloq.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Slouch</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Slouch
<hw>Slouch</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To cause to hang down; to depress
at the side; <as>as, to <ex>slouth</ex> the hat</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Slouching</ent>⟦br⟧
